 Predictive Analytics Using Historical Data

Project Overview

This project focuses on building predictive models using historical data to forecast future trends and support data-driven decision-making.

Objectives

* Analyze historical datasets.
* Clean and preprocess data.
* Build predictive models using regression and time-series techniques.
* Forecast future trends.
* Evaluate model performance and accuracy.

 Key Features

* Data cleaning and preprocessing.
* Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA).
* Regression-based prediction models.
* Time-series forecasting.
* Model evaluation and performance metrics.
* Visualization of predictions and trends.

 Tools Used

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Scikit-learn
* Matplotlib
* Jupyter Notebook

 Methodology

1. Collect historical data.
2. Clean and preprocess the dataset.
3. Perform exploratory data analysis.
4. Train predictive models.
5. Generate forecasts.
6. Evaluate model accuracy.
7. Visualize results.

 Expected Outcome

Gain practical experience in predictive modeling, trend analysis, and forecasting using historical datasets.

## Conclusion

Predictive analytics helps organizations anticipate future trends, improve planning, and make informed business decisions using data-driven insights.
